                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "comment": "Intro text",
                        "text": "An icon of the late war, the Panzerfaust was the first ever single-use anti-tank weapons in history. It's configuration of a warhead propelled by a disposable tube was copied around the world, and is still in successful use to this day. Developed by Hugo Schneider AG, the exceptionally simple and economic design allowed it to be manufactured in astronomica numbers, being deployed to millions of German troops during the Second World War. The \"Tank Fist\" as it was known, was higly effective against contemporary enemy armor when deployed in close-quaters situation. It's portability granted quick and dynamic deployments, it's [[HEAT]] warheads provided over 200mm of penetrative performance, more than enough to handle anything in its, admittidely small path.\n\nIn ARMA III, the [[spearhead1944]] DLC provides both the Panzerfaust 30 (Gross, lit. Large) and the Panzerfaust 60 variants, each named after it's effective range in meters."
                    },

